sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K242900
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
This is a device for killing the cell if phage T3 or T7 is inside the cell.
RNA pol of T3 and T7 recognize the promoter and transcribe the toxic domain of colicin E3 and E9.
Also you transcribe LuxI, an AHL productor.
We expect high level of transcription with this promoter and polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Until not expected, basal transcription of the toxins could be a problem. Those promoter recognized by T3 and T7 RNApol are not recognized by E.Coli -in theory-.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Enrique Paz

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K242201
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Escherichia coli strain J plasmid ColE9-J
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Colicin E9 is able to degrade DNA. This DNase domain extracted by us is enough to get this function. It is inhibited in the presence of its immunity protein 9.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We took the sequence designed by Russell WALLIS et al. We included a RBS, eliminated preffix/suffix restriction sites and added two stop codons (ATT).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Jes??s Abraham Avelar Rivas

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K242200
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Colicin E3 is a bacteriocin targeting 16S rRNA in the 30S subunit at a single and specific site near to the 3' terminus. We extracted the ribonuclease domain which is enough for degrading RNA. Inhibited when Im3 is present
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Just adapted the reported sequence to iGEM standarized sequence.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Jes??s Abraham Avelar Rivas

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K242101
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: GFP induced by T7/T3 RNA polymerases
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The detection of the RNA polymerases from both T3 or T7 bacteriophages will make the cells containing this biobrick to express GFP.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We want to have a reporter when the phage infects our cells.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Laura Gomez, Uriel Urquiza

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: luxI
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Synthesizes 3OC6HSL, which binds to LuxR.

The lux cassette of V. fischeri contains a left and a right promoter. The right promoter gives weak constitutive expression of downstream genes.This expression is up-regulated by the action of the Lux repressor, LuxR. Two molecules of LuxR protein form a complex with two molecules the signalling compound HSL. This complex binds to a palindromic site on the promoter, increasing the rate of transcription.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: An LVA tail (sequence: AANDENYALVA) was added to increase protein degradation. .
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr
